# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you shouldn't ignore these files, but for a specific
#   project, it can be useful to ignore them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1188, it is a recommended practice to PC commit and share the lockfile.
#   However, if you're building an app and not a library, you should commit it.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-pyprojectlock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
